ABUJA (SundiataPost) – With additional 182 new infections on Thursday, Nigeria’s confirmed COVID-19 cases have reached 8,915. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released the new figures through its Twitter handle @NCDCgov on Thursday night. Lagos, the epicentre of the virus in Nigeria has 111 out of the 182 new cases. The rest are shared by 14 states and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. The number of discharged patients stand at 2,592 while the number of deaths resulting from the virus is 259. The details are as follows: Lagos-111FCT-16Akwa Ibom-10Oyo-8Kaduna-6Delta-6Rivers-5Ogun-4Ebonyi-4Kano-3Plateau-2Gombe-2Kebbi-1Kwara-2Bauchi-1Borno-1 8915 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 2592Deaths: 259 https://t.co/j23D8XfjOk ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - The COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria took a different turn on Thursday as Kano State overtook Lagos in the number of new infections. According to the daily update by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released late on Thursday, there were 204 new cases of the pandemic out… May 1, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Lagos State, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano and Oyo have spiked the number Nigeria's confirmed Coronavirus cases with the addition of 35 confirmed infections as at late Thursday night.Lagos State has 19 new infections with FCT contributing nine. Kano and Oyo have five and two new cases respectively… April 16, 2020 In "Top Stories"